<p class="noPspace header">What is a Journey Host?</p>
<p class="noPspace">Being a host means that you welcome a small group of 6-12 people into your home&mdash;or another suitable spot&mdash;for six weeks. You don&rsquo;t need to have all the answers, and we don&rsquo;t expect you to be a Bible expert or therapist. Just be friendly, inclusive, a quiet leader and a good role model.</p>
<p class="noPspace">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="noPspace subheading">We&rsquo;ll equip you with a Host Kit and Handbook, but here are some ideas of what you&rsquo;ll be asked to do:</p>
<p class="noPspace subheading">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="noPspace subheading"><span style="color: #292929; font-family: &rsquo;Helvetica Neue&rsquo;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: 1.75;">-Help set some ground rules. We&rsquo;ll give you some ideas to discuss with the group at your first meeting.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="noPspace"><span>-Be a timekeeper. Just be sure your group is starting and ending at the agreed upon time.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="noPspace"><span>-Bring everyone into the conversation. If you notice someone being quiet, ask if they&rsquo;d like to give some input.</span></p>
<p class="noPspace"><span>-Make it safe&mdash;respect any and all questions.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="noPspace"><span>-Feel free to pray for your group during group time.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="noPspace"><span>-Did we mention have fun? Have some.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="noPspace"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr"><span class="sectionHeader">Host Orientation</span></p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">Are you a new host? We recommend you try this out for tips and more. Childcare not provided.</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">OAKLEY- Saturday, October 5, 9AM-12PM</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">FLORENCE- Saturday, October 12, 9AM-12PM</p>
<p class="noPspace" dir="ltr">MASON- Saturday, October 12, 9AM-12PM</p>
